assets.name: assets/8VXt1OQ3vML
assets.description:
GALANTE SHOP, located behind the cathedral, before the arch.
The owner, after the fall of Napoleon and the abandonment of the city by the Franco-Polish troops, wanted to make an incision on the doorposts of the shop, to remind posterity that "IN THE YEAR OF THE LORD 1798, TERRACINA WAS SACKED ON DAY 19 AUGUST FROM THE FRENCH "
